The original code had a serious bug: `event::read()?` was being called TWICE. The else-if branch would call `event::read()` again, which would actually block waiting for a new event! This is a real bug fix, not just a style improvement.

The new code:
```rust
match event::read()? {
    Event::Key(key) => {
        if handle_key_event(state, key)? {
            break;
        }
    }
    Event::Resize(_, _) => {
        // Terminal resized, will re-render on next loop
    }
    _ => {}
}
```

